<HEADLINE>
<P>
HEALTH PLAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Re "Key Element of Clinton's Health Plan Passes First Test" (March 16): 
</P>
<P>
 The fact that the first congressional subcommittee to consider health 
legislation reform proposed that employers be required to pay 80% of health 
insurance costs for their workers is not too surprising. Don't taxpayers pay 
roughly 75% of the health insurance costs for federal government employees? 
</P>
<P>
 A 60%/40% employer/employee payment ratio might be more practical, 
particularly for smaller businesses, and better for the business economy in 
general, but then representatives would be proposing higher insurance costs for 
themselves -- and for all state government employees as well. 
</P>
<P>
 ETELVINA R. PATMAS 
</P>
<P>
 Orange 
</P>
<P>
 * To those who favor a government-administered health plan, I have two 
questions: Would you like it administered by the post office? If you have any 
complaints, would you like them handled by the IRS? Enough said. 
</P>
<P>
 GARY A. ROBB 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
