<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWS BITES: HOWCUM 2NITE ISSO DFFRNT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DANIEL NUSSBAUM, Los Angeles-based writer Daniel Nussbaum has assigned 
himself the task of translating the key texts of world civilization into the 
language of California's vanity license plates. In the following passage, 
Nussbaum uses 64 actual plates to adapt the moment in the Passover Seder when 
the youngest child at the table asks, Why is this night different from all 
other nights? PL8SPK, a collection of the writer's vanity plate translations, 
has been published by HarperCollinsWest. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 HOWCUM 2NITE ISSO TOE2LY DFFRNT FFRROMM ALLL OTHERR 1S? 
</P>
<P>
 EVRYNYT, IPH WE WANNA, WECAN EET BREAD OR MATZOHS; YIZZIT TONITE ITZ MATZO 
ORELSE? 
</P>
<P>
 USULI ATNIGHT WEWILL GO4 DISNDAT HHERB, WUTEVR; TELLMEY ONN THISSS NIGHTT 
WEHAVE2 MUNCHON BITTER HERBZ. 
</P>
<P>
 DURING ORDNARY NIGHTS WEDON'T DIP THE HERBS EVEN ONCE; SOWHY SUDNLEE RWE 
DOINIT TWICE? 
</P>
<P>
 EVERY OTHA NIGHT WEALL SUP, PERHAPS SITTIN UP, PERHAPS KIKNBAK; TOONIGHT WHYY 
DO ALLOVUS KIKBAKK? DANIEL NUSSBAUM 
</P>
