<HEADLINE>
<P>
POLICE BLOTTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 ALHAMBRA: Officers took three suspects into custody early Friday morning for 
auto burglary. The Los Angeles teen-agers were arrested about 3:20 a.m. after 
neighbors saw them stealing stereos out of cars parked in the 400 block of 
North Electric Avenue and called 911, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 ARCADIA: A man was followed home Monday night and robbed at gunpoint as he 
backed his car into his garage in the 400 block of Cambridge Drive, police 
said. Two men, both about 18 years old, confronted the man about 7:40 p.m. as 
he was returning home from dinner at the food court at President's Square. They 
stole about $150 in cash, police said. No injuries were reported and no arrests 
wer e made. 
</P>
<P>
 ARCADIA: Police held a press conference Thursday to ask for the public's help 
in solving a fatal hit-and-run accident. On March 6, Arcadia resident Shaowu 
Yen, 79, was struck by a red Toyota or Nissan pickup truck with a white camper 
shell as he stood at Holly and Fairview avenues. Yen died later that day at 
Arcadia Methodist Hospital. Police have asked anyone with information about the 
accident to call 574-5150. The Yen family and the Arcadia Chinese Assn. are 
together offering a $10,000 reward for the capture of the driver. 
</P>
<P>
 AZUSA: A 23-year-old Los Angeles man was robbed at gunpoint Saturday as he got 
off a bus at Mauna Loa and Citrus avenues, police said. Two suspects described 
by police as gang members pulled up to the man in a gray pickup and stole his 
wallet after they pointed a handgun at him. No injuries were reported and no 
arrests have been made. 
</P>
<P>
 EL MONTE: A man who apparently swallowed a quantity of cocaine to hide the 
drug from officers as he was being arrested died early Friday at Greater El 
Monte Community Hospital. The 27-year-old San Gabriel man, whose name was 
withheld pending notification of relatives, died at the hospital at 3 a.m., 
police said. He was arrested during a drug investigation at 10177 Valley Blvd. 
</P>
<P>
 POMONA: A man who was shot and stabbed early Sunday morning died of his 
injuries early Tuesday, police said. David Fraire, 24, of West Covina 
apparently got into a gang-related fight with Edward Dominguez, 19, of San 
Gabriel about 1:09 a.m. at a residence on Indian Hill Boulevard. Shots were 
fired, and officers arrived to find Fraire with a shotgun wound to his stomach, 
a gunshot wound to his back and a stab wound to his chest. Dominguez had two 
stab wounds to his left arm. Both were rushed to the hospital, police said. 
Fraire died at 5 a.m. Tuesday at Pomona Valley Hospital Medical Center. . . . A 
fight in the parking lot of a Pomona gas station ended in gunfire, leaving a 
man dead. Daniel Belmudes, 33, of Pomona, was pronounced dead on arrival at 
Pomona Valley Hospital Medical Center shortly after he was shot at 2475 S. 
Garey Ave. about 10:30 p.m. on March 16. No arrests have been made. Police are 
looking for several men who fled the gas station after the shooting. 
</P>
<P>
 SAN GABRIEL: A man who allegedly ran over his ex-girlfriend with his car in 
San Gabriel on March 15 was arrested in Las Cruces, N.M., the next day. Jian 
Wei Zhao, 38, of Monterey Park allegedly rammed Qiu Zhai, 38, about 10 p.m. as 
she was walking home. 
</P>
</TEXT>
