<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: SCHAEFER TRAILS ROBINGS IN FUNDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CARLOS V. LOZANO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ventura County supervisorial candidate Madge L. Schaefer has raised $5,848 
since the beginning of the year, while opponent H. Jere Robings reported a cash 
total of $13,770, including a $10,000 personal loan, according to recent 
finance statements. 
</P>
<P>
 The two were among several Ventura County candidates whose campaign finance 
statements were received Wednesday by the county elections office.Other 
candidates' reports were available earlier. 
</P>
<P>
 Schaefer's single largest contribution of $1,800 came from the Public 
Employees Assn. of Ventura County. The former supervisor also loaned her 
campaign $2,000. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition to his $10,000 loan, Robings received contributions of $500 from 
various individuals and property management firms. 
</P>
<P>
 Meanwhile, Moorpark City Councilman Scott Montgomery, who is seeking the 
supervisor's seat being vacated by Vicky Howard, reported a single personal 
loan of $2,000. 
</P>
<P>
 Financial statements from two candidates for county auditor-controller also 
were received Wednesday. Simi Valley Mayor Greg Stratton, who reported $2,256 
cash on hand at the beginning of the year, showed no new contributions, and 
accountant Clifford Wigen reported a single personal loan of $5,027. A 
financial report from accountant Richard Morrisset had not been received by the 
elections office. 
</P>
<P>
 In other races, County Clerk Richard Dean, who is seeking reelection, reported 
a single personal loan of $7,943, while his opponent, Daniel Schmidt, raised 
less than $1,000. 
</P>
<P>
 In the race for county tax assessor, incumbent Glenn E. Gray loaned his 
campaign $5,889 and reported no other contributions. His opponent, Jack 
Tingstrom, raised less than $1,000. 
</P>
<P>
 Assistant Dist. Atty. Colleen Toy White, who is competing for the judicial 
seat left vacant by retired Superior Court Judge Edwin M. Osborne, reported 
total cash contributions of $4,150. The finance report of defense attorney 
James M. Farley, White's only opponent, was not immediately available. CARLOS 
V. LOZANO 
</P>
</TEXT>
