<TEXT>
<P>
 In nonleague boys' tennis: 
</P>
<P>
 El Toro 13 1/3, Fountain Valley 7 2/3 -- John France swept at No. 1 singles, 
6-0, 6-0, 6-0, to extend his school-record consecutive winning streak to 60 
sets, including 27 this season for El Toro (6-3). Fountain Valley is 5-4. 
</P>
<P>
 La Quinta 12, Mater Dei 9 -- Loi Du and Joey Nguyen won their doubles sets, 
6-4, 6-0, 6-2, to lead a sweep of doubles for La Quinta (4-1). Bret Hanke won 
his singles sets, 6-1, 6-1, 6-0, for Mater Dei (1-2). 
</P>
<P>
 Loara 13 1/3, Estancia 7 2/3 -- Ben Chung won two of his three sets, 1-6, 6-4, 
6-3, for Loara. Rob Horansky swept, 6-3, 6-1, 6-1, for Estancia. 
</P>
<P>
 Los Alamitos 21, Savanna 0 -- Alejandro Lopez swept No. 3 singles, 6-4, 6-3, 
7-6, and Joe Shih and William Chen swept No. 3 doubles, 7-5, 6-3, 6-3, to lead 
Los Alamitos (6-2). Savanna is 3-6. 
</P>
<P>
 Mission Viejo 12 1/3, Santa Margarita 9 2/3 -- Brian Gruner and Derek Toross 
swept at No. 1 doubles, 6-3, 6-1, 6-2, to lead Mission Viejo (2-5). 
</P>
