<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTH WINS GIRLS' SOCCER ALL-STAR GAME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAN ARRITT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Laguna Hills goalkeeper Sarah Lang shut down a talented front line as the 
South defeated the North, 2-0, in the Orange County girls' soccer all-star game 
Wednesday at Chapman University. 
</P>
<P>
 Lang played 90 minutes in goal, which was 10 minutes longer than a 
regular-season game, and stopped several excellent scoring chances by the 
North. 
</P>
<P>
 On offense, the South used a pair of unassisted goals on outstanding 
individual efforts by San Clemente's Jaime Greiner and Edison's Christine 
Tyler. 
</P>
<P>
 Greiner gave the South a 1-0 lead 20 minutes into the game when she ran down a 
pass, maneuvered around a North defender and beat El Modena goalkeeper Amy 
Moreno up high. 
</P>
<P>
 Shortly before the half, Lang made the biggest save of the game, diving to her 
left to tip away a shot by Capistrano Valley's Lindsay Light. 
</P>
<P>
 Lang stopped two more open shots in the second half and also used her height 
to foil several North corner kicks late in the game. 
</P>
<P>
 With a minute to play, the South cushioned its lead when Tyler trapped a goal 
kick from Moreno at midfield and took off on a breakaway. Moreno came toward 
Tyler, but Tyler's shot was too high and hard, skipping off Moreno's hands and 
into the goal. DAN ARRITT 
</P>
</TEXT>
