<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP NOTES: FOUNTAIN VALLEY'S BILLINGSLEY CHANGES MIND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL ITAGAKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Gordon Billingsley said Wednesday he will remain as the Fountain Valley boys' 
basketball coach. Athletic Director Mike Henigan announced Monday that 
Billingsley had resigned. 
</P>
<P>
 "I talked with some of the kids . . . Brandon Leimbach told me I was crazy to 
quit," Billingsley said. "But the decision to quit wasn't a spur of the moment 
thing. 
</P>
<P>
 "A few weeks ago, I told Mike I would resign. I didn't quit because I was 
tired of coaching, but it was more of a frustration thing. I haven't had anyone 
on campus to help out with the lower-level programs and I think those kids get 
cheated. 
</P>
<P>
 "But I figured I've done this for five years by myself so I'll do it for a 
couple of more years," Billingsley said.  
</P>
<P>
 Billingsley is 64-65 at Fountain Valley, leading the Barons to the Southern 
Section Division I-AA quarterfinals this season, where they lost on a 
last-second shot to eventual-champion Long Beach Poly, 50-48. The Barons won 
their first Sunset League championship in Billingsley's five-year tenure. 
MICHAEL ITAGAKI 
</P>
</TEXT>
