<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; TITANS BEAT WICHITA STATE ON LATE SQUEEZE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Brian Loyd's bases loaded suicide squeeze with one out in the bottom of the 
13th gave Cal State Fullerton a 5-4 victory over Wichita State Wednesday night 
at Titan Field. 
</P>
<P>
 Wichita State led 2-0 going into the bottom of the eighth before Fullerton's 
D.C. Olsen led the inning off with a home run. 
</P>
<P>
 Trailing, 2-1, in the bottom of the ninth the Titans were able to tie the 
score on another home run, this one by Tony Miranda. 
</P>
<P>
 Wichita State scored twice in the top of the 12th to take a 4-2 lead but 
Fullerton tied it in the bottom of the inning on a two-run single by 
pinch-hitter Robert Matos. 
</P>
<P>
 Matt Wagner recorded his fifth victory of the year for the Titans. 
</P>
<P>
 Miranda had four hits for the Titans (21-5). Wichita State drops to 11-7. 
</P>
<P>
 In other nonconference baseball: 
</P>
<P>
 Pacific Lutheran 4, Southern California College 3 -- Pacific Lutheran scored 
two unearned runs in the seventh inning off Southern California College 
reliever Augie Pena, who took over for starter Ila Borders. 
</P>
<P>
 Borders, who received no decision, pitched six innings, allowing two runs and 
seven hits, striking out one with no walks. 
</P>
<P>
 Pena (1-2) retired the first two batters of the seventh before a single, a 
bad-hop error by shortstop Jason Brissey and two more singles scored the runs. 
</P>
<P>
 Host SCC (9-17), which had seven hits, scored single runs in the first, second 
and fourth innings. Two came on wild pitches and one on a sacrifice fly by Ken 
Turner. 
</P>
<P>
 In the PONY softball tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 Cal State Fullerton 7, Florida State 0 -- Freshman Trinity Johnson pitched a 
four-hitter for the Titans in pool play. The Titans (12-16) lost to 
Northwestern, 9-1, in another pool-play game. The game was shortened to six 
innings because of the mercy rule. 
</P>
<P>
 Northwestern 9, Cal State Fullerton 1 (6, mercy) -- Jena Sansone had two hits 
and two RBIs for Northwestern (12-5). 
</P>
<P>
 In women's tennis: 
</P>
<P>
 Cal State Fullerton 5, Georgia Tech 3 -- Christa Hanson won in singles, 7-5, 
5-7, 7-5, then teamed with Jennifer Canfield at No. 3 doubles to win, 6-4, 7-6 
for the Titans (5-11). Georgia Tech is 5-10. 
</P>
