<HEADLINE>
<P>
BASEBALL DAILY REPORT; AROUND THE MAJORS; CARTER BREAKS RIGHT THUMB, EXPECTED 
TO BE OUT A MONTH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Joe Carter of the Toronto Blue Jays is expected to be sidelined for at least a 
month because of a broken right thumb, the result of being struck by a pitch 
from Scott Erickson of the Minnesota Twins during a 12-9 victory Wednesday at 
Dunedin, Fla. 
</P>
<P>
 Carter, whose three-run homer against Mitch Williams of the Philadelphia 
Phillies last fall in the bottom of the ninth inning of Game 6 gave the Blue 
Jays their second consecutive World Series championship, was not believed to be 
seriously injured at first. The break was discovered during postgame X-rays. 
</P>
