<P>
 After more than a decade, the celebrated Air Guitar show at Capistrano Valley 
High School in Mission Viejo has been canceled. 
</P>
<P>
 Only eight groups auditioned, even though the tryout date was extended to 
increase participation.And that wasn't enough to put together a good show, 
according to the student newspaper, the CVHS Times. 
</P>
<P>
 Meanwhile, nine students who had opted to attend the new Aliso Niguel High 
School, touted as a state-of-the-art facility, have decided to return to 
Capistrano Valley after one semester, according to the newspaper.  
</P>
<P>
 "The only advanced technology they had was the Dinacom system, which wasn't 
even available to use until after Christmas. I do have to say that the 
skylights were pretty neat, though," one student said. 
