<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: BEVERLY HILLS; PLANNING COMMISSION HEAD NAMED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Beverly Hills Planning Commission has elected member Hamid Gabbay as its 
chairman. 
</P>
<P>
 Gabbay, an architect, replaces Paul Selwyn, who in April must step down after 
completing his second four-year term, the maximum allowed by the city. 
</P>
<P>
 A 15-year resident who lives in the city's Hillside District, Gabbay was 
appointed to the commission in 1992. He will be chairman for one year. He 
previously served on the now-defunct R-1 Commission, which had reviewed 
applications for single-family homes. Those duties were transferred to the 
Planning Commission in December, 1992. 
</P>
</TEXT>
