<TEXT>
<P>
 A 24-year-old man who was stabbed in the neck during an argument behind a 
fast-food restaurant is expected to survive his wound, but his three attackers 
remained at large Wednesday, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 The stabbing occurred at 5:20 p.m. Tuesday at Del Taco, 22401 El Toro Road, 
said Sheriff's Lt. Dan Martini. 
</P>
<P>
 The victim, Harold Rama Corzano of Lake Forest, was taken to Mission Hospital 
Regional Medical Center in Mission Viejo, where he is in good condition, a 
hospital spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
 Witnesses said Corzano was arguing with three men when one of them stabbed him 
on the right side of his neck, severing an artery, Martini said. 
</P>
<P>
 After the stabbing, the attackers jumped over a block wall fence and fled. 
They may have left the scene in a white Honda, a large black truck, or both, 
Martini said. 
