<TEXT>
<P>
 Caserta Steps Aside as President of Spectrum: The head of Spectrum Information 
Technologies Inc. stepped aside, adding to the uncertainty over the small 
company that briefly shared the spotlight with former Apple Computer Inc. boss 
John Sculley.Spectrum said Peter T. Caserta was taking an indefinite leave of 
absence so he can clear his name since the arrests Tuesday of five men linked 
to another company he started and recently sold. Caserta could not be reached 
for comment. He was not named in the criminal fraud indictment of the current 
and former executives of Paradigm Group, formerly Caserta Group, which Caserta 
sold in January. 
</P>
