<TEXT>
<P>
 Five-Year Treasury Notes Yield Rises: Yields on the five-year Treasury notes 
rose at auction to the highest level in 15 months.The high yield was 5.91%, up 
from 5.61% at the last auction on Feb. 24. It was the highest auction rate 
since five-year note yields hit 6.03% on Dec. 23, 1992. The notes will carry a 
coupon rate of 5.875% with each $10,000 in face value selling for $9,985.00. A 
total of $11 billion in notes were sold out of bids totaling $28.1 billion. 
</P>
