<P>
ORANGE COUNTY EARNINGS: ADVANTAGE LIFE REPORTS 3RD-QUARTER NET LOSS OF $698,000 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Advantage Life Products Inc., a Laguna Hills marketer of health and beauty 
products, reported a third-quarter net loss of $697,938, or 7 cents a share, 
compared with a loss of $449,348, or 7 cents a share, for the corresponding 
period last year.Revenue for the quarter ended Jan. 31 rose to $271,136 from 
$158,927. The company reduced its loss for the nine-month period to $818,648, 
or 9 cents a share, from last fiscal year's net loss of $915,651, or 15 cents a 
share. Revenue increased to $1.7 million from $1.5 million. 
</P>
