<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: MARKETING AND MEDIA; KOCE-TV WILL AIR IN-DEPTH SERIES ON CAPITALIST 
SYSTEM IN 3 COUNTRIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Anne Michaud / Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 KOCE-TV Channel 50, the public broadcasting station of Coast Community College 
District, on March 31 will begin airing "Challenge to America," a four-part 
series that compares capitalism as it is practiced in the United States, 
Germany and Japan. 
</P>
<P>
 The series, which is new to KOCE, is hosted by Pulitzer Prize-winning 
journalist Hedrick Smith, author of "The Power Game," a description of the 
inner workings of Washington. 
</P>
<P>
 The program goes on location to the boardrooms, factories and classrooms of 
the three featured countries. The segments begin at 8 p.m. on consecutive 
Thursdays. 
</P>
<P>
 "Our mission is education," said KOCE's Roberta Smith, director of 
programming. "So this fits with our desire to air in-depth discussion, business 
and ethical issues." 
</P>
</TEXT>
