<P>
ADVANCED LOGIC WINS COMPUTER PATENT; SHARES RISE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Computer maker Advanced Logic Research Inc. saw its shares rise 16% Wednesday 
after the company announced late Tuesday that it had won an important computer 
patent. 
</P>
<P>
 ALR shares rose $1 to close at $7.125 on Nasdaq Wednesday.David Kirkey, vice 
president of worldwide marketing, said the company believes it has an important 
patent for upgrading a personal computer's obsolete microprocessor, or main 
computing brain, to a faster component. 
</P>
<P>
 ALR launched its upgradeable computers in 1989 and has reaped additional sales 
because the technology lets computer users run the latest software programs. 
</P>
<P>
 Safi Qureshey, chief executive of AST Research Inc. in Irvine, said he 
believed AST had its own resources and patents to protect itself in case ALR 
tried to enforce the patent against his company. 
</P>
