<HEADLINE>
<P>
YES, YOU HAVE SEEN THE RINK IN 'D2' BEFORE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 When "D2 The Mighty Ducks" gets to its climactic scenes, local hockey fans may 
find themselves doing a double take. 
</P>
<P>
 The film's big game, in which the Ducks square off against the imposing 
Icelandic team in an international tournament, was filmed at Anaheim Arena.The 
rink is home to the first-year National Hockey League team known as the Mighty 
Ducks, the Walt Disney Co.-owned franchise named after the company's 1992 
sleeper film hit about a misfit, overachieving crew of young skaters. 
</P>
<P>
 "D2," opening Friday, is the sequel to that film. This time around, the young 
bunch is tapped to represent the United States in the Junior Goodwill Games and 
heads from its native Minnesota to Southern California -- only to be seduced by 
the local lifestyle, leaving coach Emilio Estevez to whip them back into shape. 
</P>
<P>
 The production was filmed at Anaheim Arena for several days in July, drawing 
some 12,000 unpaid extras for one day of shooting when filmmakers needed a full 
crowd. The crew returned to re-shoot a few scenes in August, temporarily 
displacing the professional Mighty Ducks during training camp. 
</P>
<P>
 Fans of the Mighty Ducks -- the NHL team -- can hardly have missed the fact 
that the sequel is coming. A lengthy promotional trailer for the film has been 
a featured attraction at home games. 
</P>
</TEXT>
