<TEXT>
<P>
 Discrimination suit -- The Times incorrectly reported last Friday that the 
Albert Einstein College of Medicine of Yeshiva University had settled a sex 
discrimination lawsuit in which it agreed to pay $900,000 to Dr. Heidi 
Weissmann.Montefiore Medical Center, where Weissmann was employed, is 
responsible for the settlement award, not the college. The college has an 
affiliation agreement with the hospital and Weissmann had unpaid faculty status 
at the medical school because of her employment with Montefiore. The article 
also misidentified hospital attorney Philip R. Forlenza as counsel for the 
college. 
</P>
